#. translators: 1: plugin author’s website, 2: WordPress.org URL for reviews
#: templates/settings.php:1616
msgid "This is my first published plugin for WordPress so I’d appreciate any positive or negative <a href=\"%1$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">feedback</a> or leave your thoughts in a <a href=\"%2$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">review</a>. So if you have any comments or feature requests, please feel free to <a href=\"%1$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">get in touch</a> with me."
msgstr "This is my first published plugin for WordPress, so I’d appreciate any positive or negative <a href=\"%1$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">feedback</a>, or leave your thoughts in a <a href=\"%2$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">review</a>. So, if you have any comments or feature requests, please feel free to <a href=\"%1$s\" class=\"components-external-link\" target=\"_blank\">get in touch</a> with me."

#: templates/settings.php:1614
msgid "To keep the reviews current, the Places API is called at regular intervals with new relevant reviews added to the catalog over time. The extensive Shortcode can be used in any post, or page or try the Widget to place directly into the sidebar or footer. Any Shortcode parameters will overwrite the default settings in the first tab. I have kept the style sheet minimal to allow for your customizations — as a web developer/designer, this is what I’d like to see for all plugins."
msgstr "To keep the reviews current, the Places API is called at regular intervals with new relevant reviews added to the catalogue over time. The extensive shortcode can be used in any post or page, or try the widget to place directly into the sidebar or footer. Any shortcode parameters will overwrite the default settings in the first tab. I have kept the style sheet minimal to allow for your customisations – as a web developer/designer, this is what I’d like to see for all plugins."

#: templates/settings.php:1613
msgid "This review plugin came about as a consequence of collecting a business’s opening times for a London-based web client. There was plenty of relevant data for the business offered by the Places API from Google — with data from Google Maps and Google My Business. The recent review data is available and, with some tweaks, it could be displayed anywhere in a similar style to Google’s reviews pop-up in the search results."
msgstr "This review plugin came about as a consequence of collecting a business’ opening times for a London-based web client. There was plenty of relevant data for the business offered by the Places API from Google – with data from Google Maps and Google My Business. The recent review data is available and, with some tweaks, it could be displayed anywhere in a similar style to Google’s reviews pop-up in the search results."

